CALIFORNIA IN BRIEF; 
LA JOLLA; 
FRAUD DEFENDANT TELLS OF ROMANCE 
A teary Nancy Hoover Hunter testified that she initially did not like J. David 
Dominelli but fell in love with him after hearing about his impoverished 
childhood and time in Vietnam. Hunter is charged with 197 counts of fraud and 
tax evasion in connection with her work at Dominelli's J. David &amp; Co., the 
heart of Dominelli's fraudulent investment empire. Dominelli is serving a 
20-year prison term after admitting he bilked investors out of $80 million. The 
company was forced into bankruptcy by disgruntled investors in 1984. 
